import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { Button, Segment, Search, Grid, Icon } from 'semantic-ui-react';

const _MovieGenres = props => {

    return (
        <Grid>
            <Grid.Row>
                <Grid.Column width={11} verticalAlign="middle" style={{padding:'0px'}}>
                    <Grid columns='equal'>
                        <Grid.Row textAlign="right">
                            <Grid.Column>
                                <Icon name="line graph" color="olive" />Trends Now
                            </Grid.Column>
                            <Grid.Column>
                                <Icon name="fire" color="orange" />Poupular
                            </Grid.Column>
                            <Grid.Column>
                                <Icon name="bullhorn" color="teal" />Promotions
                            </Grid.Column>
                            <Grid.Column>
                                <Icon name="film" color="green" />Showtimes
                            </Grid.Column>
                            <Grid.Column>
                                <Icon name="calendar check outline" color="blue" />Bookings
                            </Grid.Column>
                        </Grid.Row>
                    </Grid>
                </Grid.Column>
                <Grid.Column width={5} verticalAlign="middle">
                    <Search
                        showNoResults={false}
                        className="customSearch"
                        onSearchChange={props.onSearchHandler}
                        placeholder="Search..." />
                </Grid.Column>
            </Grid.Row>
        </Grid>

    )
}
export default _MovieGenres
